    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="830"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d830">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/2442</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Welles</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Secretary of the Treasury</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgenthau</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-07">February 7,
                            1940</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I am glad to acknowledge your
                    letter of February 7, with which you were good enough to enclose a copy of a
                    letter which you had received under date of February 6 from the Ambassador of
                    Colombia.</p>
                <p>Let me say again how pleased I am with the result obtained by the Governmental
                    committee and how helpful I believe the conferences held in your office have in
                    fact been. I am most indebted to you for your unfailing cooperation in this and
                    in all other questions.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
